headlines.description: Tyrann Mathieu returned a punt 92 yards for a score, LSU punished third-ranked Arkansas with 286 yards rushing, and the top-ranked Tigers secured a spot in the SEC championship game with a 41-17 victory Friday.

events.name: Houston Cougars at Tulsa Golden Hurricane

headlines.description: Case Keenum threw for 457 yards and five touchdowns, Patrick Edwards had 181 yards receiving and four scores and No. 8 Houston earned a spot in the Conference USA championship game by beating Tulsa 48-16 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Keenum tosses 5 TDs in Houston's 12th win

headlines.description: Rex Burkhead, who started the week with his right foot in a walking boot, ran for 160 yards and a touchdown on a school-record 38 carries and Nebraska (No. 21 BCS, No. 22 AP) defeated Iowa 20-7 on Friday.

events.name: Eastern Michigan Eagles at Northern Illinois Huskies
Louisville Cardinals at South Florida Bulls

headlines.shortLinkText: Louisville's victory clinches share of Big East

events.name: Kent State Golden Flashes at Temple Owls
Bowling Green Falcons at Buffalo Bulls
Akron Zips at Western Michigan Broncos
Toledo Rockets at Ball State Cardinals

headlines.description: Coleman Petersen missed a 48-yard field goal try with two seconds remaining as Colorado escaped with a 17-14 victory over Utah on Friday, ending the Utes' hopes for a Pac-12 South title and halting the Buffaloes' school-record 23-game road losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: No Pac-12 title game for Utah

events.name: Boston College Eagles at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: Luke Kuechly ran an interception back for a touchdown and became Boston College's all-time tackles leader, and the Eagles picked Jacory Harris off four times in his final college game en route to beating Miami 24-17 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: BC picks off Harris four times, puts away Miami

events.name: Pittsburgh Panthers at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Shawne Alston rushed for two second-half touchdowns, including a 1-yarder with 6:10 left, and West Virginia came from 10 points down to beat Pittsburgh 21-20 on Friday night.

events.name: California Golden Bears at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.shortLinkText: Anderson's 3 TDs lead Cal past Arizona State
